        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "Reject unsupported diagnostics OTel grpc config",
        "body": "## Summary\n\nFixes #93069.\n\nThe diagnostics-otel runtime only starts for `http/protobuf`, but the config schema, generated help, and configuration reference still accepted or advertised `grpc`. This aligns those surfaces with the runtime contract so operators learn at config validation time instead of after exporter startup silently fails.\n\nEnvironment overrides still fail closed through the existing unsupported-protocol diagnostic path, because `OTEL_EXPORTER_OTLP_PROTOCOL` can come from outside OpenClaw config validation.\n\n## Verification\n\n- `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs src/config/schema.help.quality.test.ts src/config/schema.test.ts src/config/validation.allowed-values.test.ts`\n- `git diff --check`",
